          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "title": "How long will it take to see results?",
            "content": "<p>Most customers notice a difference from the very first use. The calming scent of lavender, chamomile, and valerian works immediately to help you relax and fall asleep faster. With consistent nightly use, sleep quality continues to improve over the first 1–2 weeks.</p>"
          }
        },
        "accordion_bPKVgG": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Is it safe to use every night?",
            "content": "<p>Yes. Our formula contains only natural botanical extracts — no synthetic chemicals, no melatonin, no drugs. Unlike prescription sleep aids, Good Night Pillow Mist is non-habit forming and carries zero risk of dependency. It's designed for nightly use.</p>"
          }
        },
        "accordion_PExgrx": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Will it stain my pillow or bedding?",
            "content": "<p>No. Our formula is specifically designed to absorb quickly without leaving stains, residue, or oily marks on fabric. It works with all pillow types including silk, cotton, and linen.</p>"
          }
        },
        "accordion_C4D3jA": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Can I use it alongside other sleep supplements?",
            "content": "<p>Yes. Good Night Spray Formula is an aromatherapy product applied to your pillow, not ingested. It can be safely used alongside melatonin, magnesium, or any other supplements you currently take. Always consult your doctor if you have specific concerns.</p>"
          }
        },
        "accordion_tG4bPa": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Is it safe for children and pets?",
            "content": "<p>Our ingredients are 100% natural, however we recommend keeping the product out of reach of small children. For use around pets, consult your veterinarian. Some essential oils can be sensitive for cats in particular. Not intended for direct skin application.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
